00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:29,100
You're gonna wish you were dead, but
it takes days to die from your wound.

234
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,800
Time is on your side.

235
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:33,000
Was that a fucking setup, or what?

236
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,500
Shit. Orange got tagged?

237
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:39,100
Gut shot.

238
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:41,500
Fuck. Where's Brown?

239
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:42,800
Dead.

240
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:46,100
How did he die?

241
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:49,400
How the fuck do you think?
The cops shot him.

242
00:14:50,100 --> 00:14:51,400
This is bad.

243
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:55,100
This is so fucking bad.
Is it bad?

244
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:56,700
As opposed to good?

245
00:14:57,900 --> 00:14:59,900
Man, this is fucked up.

246
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:02,200
This is so fucked up.

247
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:05,100
Somebody fucked us up
big time, man.

248
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:11,500
- You really think we were set up?
- Do you even doubt it, man?

249
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:15,900
I don't think we got set up, I know it.
Where did all those cops come from, huh?

250
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:18,200
One minute they're not there,
and the next minute they're there.

251
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:21,400
I didn't hear any sirens.
The alarm went off, okay?

252
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,900
When an alarm goes, you got
a four-minute response time.

253
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:26,500
Unless a patrol car is cruising
that street at that moment...

254
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:29,000
you got four minutes before
they can realistically respond.

255
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:31,900
In one minute, there were
17 blue boys out there...

256
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:35,300
all knowing exactly what the fuck they
were doing, and they were all there!

257
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:39,000
Remember that second wave
that showed up in the cars?

258
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:41,600
Those were the ones responding to the
alarm, but those first motherfuckers...

259
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:44,000
they were there
and they were waitin' for us.

260
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,500
Haven't you fuckin'
thought about this?

261
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:49,200
I haven't had a chance to think.

262
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:52,500
First I was just tryin'
to get the fuck outta there.

263
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:55,400
And after we got away,
I've just been dealin' with him.

264
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:57,700
Better start thinkin' about it,
'cause that's all I'm thinkin' about.

265
00:15:57,700 --> 00:16:00,600
I wasn't even gonna come here.
I was just gonna drive off, man...

266
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,100
because whoever set us up
knows about this place.

267
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:06,900
There could've been cops here waitin'!
There could be cops comin' right now!

268
00:16:10,300 --> 00:16:13,600
Let's go in the other room.
Hey. In there.

269
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:16,000
Larry, don't leave me.

270
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:23,800
I'll be right in the other room, okay?
I'll be right there lookin' at ya.

271
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:26,300
I'm right here
lookin' at you, okay?

272
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:30,700
I'm right over there.

273
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:34,600
Larry...

274
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:36,800
I'm gonna fucking die.

275
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:38,600
Larry.

276
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:42,900
What the fuck
am I doin' here, man?

277
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:45,000
I felt funny about
this job right off.

278
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,700
As soon as I felt it I should have said,
"No, thank you," but I never listen.

279
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:50,900
Every time I ever got fucked
buying weed, the same thing.

280
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:53,500
I didn't trust the guy,
but I wanted to believe him.

281
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:56,400
If he's not lying and it really
is Thai stick, then it's great.

282
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:59,800
But it never is, and I always said that
if I felt that about a job, I'd walk.

283
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:02,900
And I didn't. I didn't
because of the fuckin' money!

284
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:05,500
What's done is done.
I need you cool.

285
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,400
Are you cool?

286
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,000
I'm cool.

287
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,900
Splash some water on your face.

288
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,400
Take a breather.

289
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:37,200
Relax. Have a cigarette.

290
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:39,200
I quit.

291
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:41,900
- All right.
- Why, you got one?

292
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:16,800
Okay, let's go through
what happened.

293
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,300
We're in the place,
everything's going fine.

294
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:21,400
Then the alarm gets tripped.

295
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:25,700
I turn around
and all these cops are outside.

296
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:31,000
You're right. It was like, bam,
I blinked my eyes and they're there.

297
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:35,300
Everybody starts going ape-shit.
Then Mr. Blonde starts to shoot all--

298
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:38,200
- That's not correct.
- What's wrong with it?

299
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:41,900
Okay. The cops did not show up
after the alarm went off.

300
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:45,300
The cops didn't show up until after
Mr. Blonde started shootin' everybody.

301
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:48,400
- Soon as I heard the alarm, I saw cops.
- It wasn't that soon.

302
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:52,200
They didn't let their presence be known
until after Mr. Blonde became a madman.

303
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:55,100
I'm not sayin' they weren't there.
I'm sayin' they were there.

304
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:58,900
But they didn't make a move until after
Mr. Blonde started shootin' everybody.

305
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:01,800
I mean, that's how
I know we were set up.

306
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:05,100
- Mr. White, you can see that--
- Enough of this "Mr. White" shit.

307
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,600
Wait! Don't tell me you're fuckin' name!
I don't wanna know it!

308
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:11,200
Jesus Christ,
I ain't gonna tell you mine.

309
00:19:16,100 --> 00:19:18,400
You're right.
This is bad.

310
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:27,000
- How did you get out?
- I shot my way out.

311
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,400
Everybody started shootin',
so I blasted my way out of there.

312
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:37,200
Move it! Get outta the way!
Get the fuck outta the way!

313
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:40,600
Get the fuck outta the way!

314
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,700
Move it!
Get outta the way!

315
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:52,200
Jesus Christ!
What the fuck is your problem, man?

316
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:55,400
- You fuckin' asshole!
- Fuck you!

317
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,400
Move!

318
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:04,600
Jesus!

319
00:20:04,700 --> 00:20:07,100
Get outta the car!
Get the fuck outta the car!

320
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:09,300
Move it!
Move outta the way!

321
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:39,600
I tagged a couple of cops.

322
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,700
Did you kill anybody?

323
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:44,800
- A few cops.
- No real people?

324
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:46,700
Just cops.

325
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:59,500
Could you believe Mr. Blonde?

326
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:03,900
That was the most insane
fuckin' thing I have ever seen.

327
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:06,500
Why the fuck would Joe
hire a guy like that?

328
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:08,000
I don't want to kill anybody.

329
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:10,700
If I gotta get out that door
and you're standin' in my way...

330
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:13,100
one way or the other
you're gettin' outta my way.

331
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,400
That's the way I look at it.

332
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:18,000
The choice between
doin' ten years...

333
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,800
and takin' out
some stupid motherfucker...

334
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:23,700
ain't no choice at all.

335
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:26,300
But I ain't no madman, either.

336
00:21:26,300 --> 00:21:30,000
What the fuck was Joe thinkin'?
You can't work with a guy like that.

337
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:35,600
We're awful goddamn lucky he didn't
tag us when he shot the place up.

338
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:39,500
I came this close
to takin' his ass out myself.

339
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:42,400
I mean, everybody panics.
Everybody.

340
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:45,100
Things get tense.
It's human nature.

341
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:48,800
You panic. I don't care what
your name is, you can't help it.

342
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:52,500
Fuck, man, you panic on the inside,
in your head, you know?

343
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:56,700
You give yourself a couple of seconds,
get ahold of it and deal with it.

344
00:21:56,600 --> 00:21:59,600
What you don't do is start shootin' up
the place and start killin' people.

345
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:03,800
What you're supposed to do
is act like a fuckin' professional.

346
00:22:03,700 --> 00:22:08,200
A psychopath ain't a professional.
You can't work with a psychopath.

347
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:10,700
You don't know what those
sick assholes are gonna do next.

348
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:16,800
I mean, Jesus Christ, how old do you
think that black girl was? Twenty?

349
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:19,100
- Maybe 21?
- If that.

350
00:22:20,900 --> 00:22:23,500
Did you see what happened
to anybody else?

351
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:28,100
Me and Orange jumped in the car,
Brown floored it.

352
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:30,200
After that,
I don't know what went down.

353
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,200
It was every man for himself.

354
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:35,100
As far as Mr. Blonde and Mr. Blue are
concerned, I ain't got the foggiest...

355
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,200
'cause once I got out,
I never looked back.

356
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:39,200
What do you think?

357
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:42,500
What do I think? The cops either
caught 'em or killed 'em.

358
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:46,700
No chance they punched through?
You found a hole.

359
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:49,100
Yeah, and that was
a fuckin' miracle.

360
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:52,800
But even if they did get away,
then where the fuck are they?

361
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:56,000
You don't think it's possible one of 'em
got ahold of the diamonds and--

362
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:59,400
- No, no way.
- How can you be so sure?

363
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:03,100
I got the diamonds.

364
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,700
That's my boy.

365
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:15,400
- Where?
- I stashed 'em.

366
00:23:15,300 --> 00:23:19,600
If you wanna come with me,
let's go get 'em right now, this second.

367
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:23,000
'Cause I think stayin' here, man, we
should have our fuckin' heads examined.

368
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:25,000
That was the plan.
We meet here.

369
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,900
Then where the fuck is everybody?

370
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:30,100
I say the plan becomes null and void
once we found out we got a rat here.

371
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:33,000
We ain't got the slightest idea
what happened to Mr. Blonde or Mr. Blue.

372
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:35,400
They could both be dead
or maybe they're arrested.

373
00:23:35,300 --> 00:23:38,300
The cops could have 'em right now
at the station, sweatin' 'em down.

374
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:41,800
They don't know our names, but they
could be singin' about this place.

375
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:53,000
I swear to God,
I think I'm fuckin' jinxed.

376
00:23:52,900 --> 00:23:54,800
What?

377
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:59,600
Two jobs back,
it was a four-man job.

378
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:02,000
We discovered one of the team
was an undercover cop.

379
00:24:03,700 --> 00:24:05,400
No shit?

380
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,900
Thank God we discovered in time.

381
00:24:08,900 --> 00:24:12,000
We had to forget the whole thing,
just walk the fuck away from it.

382
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:15,100
So who's the rat this time?

383
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:17,000
Mr. Blue?

384
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,700
Mr. Brown?

385
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:22,900
Joe? Joe set this whole thing up.
Maybe he set it up to set it up.

386
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:26,300
I don't buy it.
Me and Joe go back a long time.

387
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:29,500
I can tell you definitely, Joe didn't
know a thing about this bullshit.

388
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:34,100
I know Joe, and me sayin' he definitely
had nothin' to do with it is ridiculous.

389
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:37,100
I can say I definitely didn't do it,
'cause I know what I did or didn't do.

390
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:40,600
But I cannot definitely say that about
anybody, 'cause I don't definitely know.

391
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:42,500
For all I know, you're the rat.

392
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:44,900
For all I know,
you're the fuckin' rat!

393
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:47,200
All right, now you're usin'
your fuckin' head.

394
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:49,600
For all we know, he's the rat.

395
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:52,900
That kid in there is dying
from a fuckin' bullet I saw him take...

396
00:24:52,900 --> 00:24:55,000
so don't you be calling him a rat!

397
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:57,300
Look, I'm right, okay?

398
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:59,800
Somebody's a fuckin' rat.

399
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:06,800
Where's the commode in this dungeon?
I gotta take a squirt.

400
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:12,400
Go down the hall, make a left,
go up the stairs...

401
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:14,300
and make a right.

402
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:25,300
- By the way, how's Alabama?
- Alabama?

403
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:28,800
I haven't seen Bama
in over a year and a half.

404
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:31,200
But I thought you two
were a team.

405
00:25:32,100 --> 00:25:34,000
We were for a little while.

406
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:37,700
Did about four jobs together,
then decided to call it quits.

407
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:39,200
Why?

408
00:25:42,100 --> 00:25:45,900
You push that woman-man thing too long
and it gets to you after a while.

409
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:47,900
What's she doin' now?

410
00:25:47,900 --> 00:25:51,400
She hooked up with Frank McGar.
They've done a couple jobs together.

411
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:53,600
Hell of a woman.
Good little thief.

412
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:00,700
- So explain the telegram.
- Five-man job.

413
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:02,800
Bustin' in and bustin' out
of a diamond wholesaler's.

414
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:05,800
Can you move the ice afterwards?
I don't know nobody that can move ice.

415
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:08,000
No problem.
We got guys waitin' for it.

416
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:11,200
What happened to Marcellus Spivey?
Didn't he always move your ice?

417
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:13,700
He's doin' 20 years in Susanville.

418
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:16,900
Twenty years? Holy God.
What for?

419
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:18,200
Bad luck.

420
00:26:18,300 --> 00:26:20,100
I guess you can say that again.

421
00:26:20,900 --> 00:26:22,800
What's the exposure like?

422
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:25,800
Two minutes, tops.
But it's a tough two minutes.

423
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:29,100
Daylight, during business hours,
dealing with a crowd.

424
00:26:29,100 --> 00:26:31,500
But you'll have the guys
to deal with the crowd.

425
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:34,400
- How many employees?
- I'd say around 20.

426
00:26:34,300 --> 00:26:36,100
Security pretty lax.

427
00:26:36,100 --> 00:26:38,500
They most usually
just deal in boxes.

428
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:41,400
You know, uncut stones
from the diamond syndicate.

429
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:46,100
But on this day, they're getting a
shipment of polished stones from lsrael.

430
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:48,200
They're like a way station,
you know?

431
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:51,500
-They get picked up and sent to Vermont.
-No, they're not.

432
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:56,700
What's the cut, poppa?

433
00:26:56,700 --> 00:27:00,300
Juicy, junior.
Real juicy.

434
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:05,400
Look, man, you do what you want.

435
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:08,100
I'm outta here, man. I'm gonna
check into a motel for a few days.

436
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:11,000
You know, I'll lay low
and I'll call Joe--

437
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,600
Shit. Did he fuckin' die on us?

438
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:17,700
Huh? ls he dead or what?

439
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:22,000
- He ain't dead.
- What is it?

440
00:27:21,900 --> 00:27:24,600
I think he's just passed out.

441
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:28,700
He scared the fuckin' shit outta me.
I thought he was dead for sure.

442
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:31,400
Without medical attention,
he will die for sure.

443
00:27:32,300 --> 00:27:35,300
What are we gonna do, man?
We can't take him to the hospital.

444
00:27:36,700 --> 00:27:40,600
Without medical attention,
he might not live through the night.

445
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:43,300
The bullet in his belly
is my fault.

446
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:47,000
While that might not mean jack shit
to you, it means a hell of a lot to me.

447
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:50,800
First things first, okay?
Stayin' here's goofy. We gotta book up.

448
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:53,300
So what do you suggest we do?
Go to a hotel?

449
00:27:53,300 --> 00:27:57,500
We got a guy who's shot in the belly,
who can't walk, bleeds like a stuck pig.

450
00:27:57,300 --> 00:27:59,700
And when he's awake,
he screams in pain.

451
00:28:00,700 --> 00:28:02,700
You got an idea, spit it out.

452
00:28:02,700 --> 00:28:04,500
Joe could help.

453
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:09,200
If we could get in touch with Joe,
Joe could get him to a doctor.

454
00:28:09,100 --> 00:28:12,100
Joe could get a doctor
to come to see him.

455
00:28:12,100 --> 00:28:16,200
Assuming we can trust Joe,
how we gonna get in touch with him?

456
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:20,000
He's supposed to be here, but he ain't,
which makes me nervous about bein' here.

457
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:23,700
Even if he is on the up and up, I don't
think he's gonna be too happy with us.

458
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:26,200
He planned a robbery and
he's got a bloodbath on his hands now.

459
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:29,500
He's got dead cops, dead robbers,
dead civilians.

460
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:32,200
I tend to doubt he's gonna have
a lot of sympathy for our plight.

461
00:28:32,100 --> 00:28:36,800
If I was him, I'd put as much distance
between me and this mess as possible.

