00:41:14,500 --> 00:41:17,400
I'll get you down in Long Beach
as a dockworker.

693
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:20,600
I don't wanna lift
no fuckin' crates, Eddie.

694
00:41:20,500 --> 00:41:24,000
You ain't gonna lift shit.
You don't even work there.

695
00:41:23,900 --> 00:41:26,900
But as far as the records
are concerned, you do.

696
00:41:26,900 --> 00:41:30,800
I call Matthews and tell him he's got
a new guy, boom, you're on the rotation.

697
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:34,700
You get a time card. It's clocked
in and out for you every day.

698
00:41:34,500 --> 00:41:39,200
At the end of the week you get a nice
paycheck. Dockworkers do very well.

699
00:41:39,100 --> 00:41:41,700
You can move into a halfway decent place
without Scagnetti goin'...

700
00:41:41,700 --> 00:41:43,900
"Where the fuck's
the money comin' from?"

701
00:41:43,900 --> 00:41:47,400
And, if he decides
to make a surprise visit...

702
00:41:47,300 --> 00:41:51,600
that's the day we sent you to Tustin
to pick up a load of shit.

703
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:54,700
If he comes back again, hey,
"Sorry, Seymour.

704
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:56,200
You just missed him.

705
00:41:56,300 --> 00:41:59,800
We had to send him to the Taft airstrip
five fuckin' hours away.

706
00:41:59,700 --> 00:42:02,400
We had a load of shit he had to
pick up there and bring back here."

707
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:06,000
Part of your job is goin' different
places. That's the beauty of it.

708
00:42:05,900 --> 00:42:08,600
We got places all over the place.

709
00:42:08,500 --> 00:42:10,700
See, Vic?
Did I tell you not to worry?

710
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:14,700
- Vic was worried.
- I'll take you to Long Beach tomorrow.

711
00:42:14,600 --> 00:42:18,500
We'll get you fixed up with Matthews,
I'll tell him what's what.

712
00:42:19,900 --> 00:42:22,700
You know, I really appreciate
what you guys are doin'...

713
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:25,300
but I'd like to know
when I can come back...

714
00:42:25,300 --> 00:42:27,500
you know, do some real work.

715
00:42:27,500 --> 00:42:29,800
Well, it's hard to say.

716
00:42:29,800 --> 00:42:32,700
It's kind of a strange time now.

717
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:35,100
Things are kind of--

718
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:38,100
They're a little fucked up,
is what they are.

719
00:42:38,100 --> 00:42:41,200
We're just gettin' ready for
a big meetin' right now in Vegas.

720
00:42:41,100 --> 00:42:45,700
Look, just let Eddie for now
set you up at Long Beach.

721
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:48,900
Get you a job,
give you some cash...

722
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:51,900
and get this Scagnetti fuck
off your back...

723
00:42:51,900 --> 00:42:55,100
and then we'll talk
to you, all right?

724
00:42:55,100 --> 00:42:56,100
Huh?

725
00:42:56,100 --> 00:42:59,800
Dad, I got an idea.

726
00:42:59,700 --> 00:43:02,500
Just hear me out.

727
00:43:02,400 --> 00:43:06,000
I know you don't like usin'
the boys on these jobs...

728
00:43:05,900 --> 00:43:10,300
but Vic here-- I mean, he's only
been nothin' but good luck for us.

729
00:43:10,200 --> 00:43:13,200
The guy's a fuckin' rabbit's foot,
for cryin' out loud.

730
00:43:14,200 --> 00:43:16,500
I'd like to have him in.

731
00:43:16,500 --> 00:43:20,100
You know he can handle himself, and
you damn sure know you can trust him.

732
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:23,600
All right, Vic...

733
00:43:23,600 --> 00:43:27,700
how would you feel about pullin'
a job with about five other guys?

734
00:43:30,100 --> 00:43:32,200
I'd feel great about it.

735
00:43:36,700 --> 00:43:40,400
K-BILLY's "Super Sounds
of the '70s" continues.

736
00:43:40,300 --> 00:43:42,400
If you're the 12th caller...

737
00:43:42,300 --> 00:43:45,800
you'll win two tickets to
the monster truck extravaganza...

738
00:43:45,700 --> 00:43:49,000
being held tonight
at the Carson Fairgrounds...

739
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:54,000
featuring Big Daddy Don Bodine's truck,
"The Behemoth."

740
00:43:53,900 --> 00:43:58,800
The 12th caller wins on the station
where the '70s survived.

741
00:44:03,400 --> 00:44:06,900
Hey, Dov, we got
a major situation here.

742
00:44:06,900 --> 00:44:10,400
I know you know that. I gotta talk to
Daddy and find out what he wants done.

743
00:44:17,700 --> 00:44:22,100
All I know is what Vic told me.
The place turned into a bullet-fest.

744
00:44:22,100 --> 00:44:24,600
He took a cop hostage
just to get the fuck outta there.

745
00:44:24,500 --> 00:44:26,400
Get up! Get up!

746
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:31,600
Do I sound like
I'm fuckin' jokin'?

747
00:44:31,500 --> 00:44:33,900
He's fuckin' drivin' around
with a cop in his trunk!

748
00:44:38,500 --> 00:44:40,400
I don't know who did what!

749
00:44:40,400 --> 00:44:43,500
I don't know who's got the loot.
I don't know if anybody's got the loot.

750
00:44:43,400 --> 00:44:47,300
I don't know who's dead, who's alive,
who's caught, who's not.

751
00:45:02,200 --> 00:45:05,200
I will know.
I'm practically there now.

752
00:45:06,300 --> 00:45:09,100
But what do I tell
these guys about Daddy?

753
00:45:11,100 --> 00:45:14,300
All right.
You sure that's what he said?

754
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:17,800
Okay, that's what I'll tell 'em.

755
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:19,800
Huh? Fuck you!

756
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:22,300
You like bein' a fuckin' hero?
You like bein' a fuckin' hero?

757
00:45:22,300 --> 00:45:23,800
You like bein' a fuckin' hero?

758
00:45:26,900 --> 00:45:29,700
You're gonna suffer
for nothin', pal.

759
00:45:29,700 --> 00:45:32,000
You hear me?
'Cause you're gonna fuckin' talk.

760
00:45:32,000 --> 00:45:34,900
- I don't fucking know anything!
- You fuckin' know.

761
00:45:34,900 --> 00:45:37,500
You know. Look at me.
You fuckin' know.

762
00:45:37,400 --> 00:45:39,800
What in the Sam Hill's
goin' on here?

763
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:42,900
- Nice Guy, we got a cop.
- Where the fuck is Joe?

764
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:46,000
Holy shit. Orange is dead.

765
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:49,900
No, he's not dead, but he will be
if we don't get him taken care of.

766
00:45:49,800 --> 00:45:52,200
We were set up.
The cops were there waitin' for us.

767
00:45:52,200 --> 00:45:54,500
What? Nobody fuckin'
set anybody up.

768
00:45:54,500 --> 00:45:56,100
The cops were there
waitin' for us.

769
00:45:56,100 --> 00:45:57,800
- Bullshit.
- Fuck you, man!

770
00:45:57,900 --> 00:46:01,200
You weren't there, we were,
and the cops had that store staked out.

771
00:46:01,100 --> 00:46:04,400
Okay, Mr. Fuckin' Detective,
you're so fuckin' smart.

772
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:07,700
- Who did it?
- We've been askin' each other!

773
00:46:07,600 --> 00:46:10,600
What'd you come up with?
You think I fuckin' set you up?

774
00:46:10,500 --> 00:46:13,300
I don't know, but somebody did.

775
00:46:14,500 --> 00:46:18,000
Nobody did. You fuckin' assholes
turned the jewelry store--

776
00:46:17,900 --> 00:46:20,900
- Don't you call me an asshole!
- You fuckin' idiot!

777
00:46:20,900 --> 00:46:22,900
Turned the jewelry store
into a wild west show...

778
00:46:22,900 --> 00:46:25,300
and you wonder why
the fuckin' cops show up?

779
00:46:26,700 --> 00:46:28,100
Where's Joseph?

780
00:46:28,200 --> 00:46:30,400
I don't know.
I ain't talked to him.

781
00:46:30,400 --> 00:46:34,800
I talked to Dov. He says Daddy's comin'
down here and he's fuckin' pissed.

782
00:46:34,700 --> 00:46:37,100
He's pissed?
I told you he'd be pissed.

783
00:46:37,100 --> 00:46:38,600
What'd Joe say?

784
00:46:38,600 --> 00:46:40,500
I told you,
I ain't talked to him!

785
00:46:40,600 --> 00:46:43,500
- All I know is he's pissed.
- What are you gonna do about him?

786
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:47,600
Give me a fuckin' chance to breathe.
I got a few questions of my own here.

787
00:46:47,500 --> 00:46:48,900
You ain't dying. He is.

788
00:46:48,900 --> 00:46:52,400
All right, Mr. Fuckin' Compassion,
I will call somebody!

789
00:46:52,300 --> 00:46:54,100
Who?

790
00:46:54,100 --> 00:46:57,600
A fuckin' snake charmer!
Who do you think? I'll call a doctor.

791
00:46:57,400 --> 00:47:01,300
They'll fix him right up.
What happened to Brown and Blue?

792
00:47:01,300 --> 00:47:03,600
Brown's dead.
We don't know what happened to Blue.

793
00:47:03,500 --> 00:47:05,400
Brown's dead? Are you sure?

794
00:47:05,400 --> 00:47:09,400
I'm sure. I was there.
He took one in the head.

795
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:11,500
Nobody's got a clue
what happened to Mr. Blue?

796
00:47:11,500 --> 00:47:13,700
Either he's alive or he's dead...

797
00:47:13,700 --> 00:47:16,700
or the cops got him
or they don't.

798
00:47:19,400 --> 00:47:21,900
I take it this is the bastard
you told me about.

799
00:47:21,900 --> 00:47:23,800
Why are you beatin' on him?

800
00:47:23,800 --> 00:47:26,200
Maybe he could tell us
who set us up.

801
00:47:26,200 --> 00:47:30,400
You beat this prick long enough, he'll
tell you he started the Chicago Fire.

802
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:33,000
Now that don't necessarily
make it fuckin' so!

803
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:35,200
Come on, man, think!

804
00:47:35,200 --> 00:47:38,600
All right,
first things fuckin' last.

805
00:47:38,600 --> 00:47:43,100
Who's got the stones? Please, somebody
tell me one little fuckin' favor.

806
00:47:42,900 --> 00:47:44,500
I got a bag.

807
00:47:44,500 --> 00:47:48,500
Okay? I stashed it 'til we could be sure
this place wasn't a police station.

808
00:47:48,500 --> 00:47:50,800
Good for you.
Now let's go get it.

809
00:47:50,800 --> 00:47:55,000
First we gotta get rid of those cars.
It looks like Sam's Hot Car Lot outside.

810
00:47:54,900 --> 00:47:55,900
Okay.

811
00:47:55,900 --> 00:47:59,800
Blondie, stay here
and baby-sit them two.

812
00:47:59,700 --> 00:48:02,400
White and Pink,
take a car each.

813
00:48:02,400 --> 00:48:06,000
I'll follow you. You ditch 'em.
Pick up the stones.

814
00:48:05,900 --> 00:48:09,000
While I'm followin' you, I'll arrange
some sort of a doctor for our friend.

815
00:48:09,000 --> 00:48:10,900
You can't leave these guys
here with him.

816
00:48:10,900 --> 00:48:14,300
- Why not?
- Because he's a fuckin' psycho.

817
00:48:15,300 --> 00:48:17,500
And if you think
Joe's pissed off...

818
00:48:17,500 --> 00:48:20,400
that ain't nothin' compared
to how pissed off I am at him...

819
00:48:20,400 --> 00:48:22,500
for puttin' me
in the same room as that bastard.

820
00:48:24,500 --> 00:48:27,000
You see what I've been
puttin' up with, Eddie?

821
00:48:26,900 --> 00:48:32,000
I fuckin' walked in here,
I told these guys about stayin' put.

822
00:48:31,900 --> 00:48:34,900
Mr. White whips out his gun,
he's stickin' it in my face...

823
00:48:34,900 --> 00:48:38,700
callin' me a motherfucker,
sayin' he's gonna blow me away...

824
00:48:38,600 --> 00:48:40,700
and blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.

825
00:48:40,700 --> 00:48:44,100
He's the reason the joint
turned into a shootin' spree.

826
00:48:44,100 --> 00:48:46,700
What are you,
a fuckin' silent partner?

827
00:48:46,700 --> 00:48:48,500
Tell him!

828
00:48:48,400 --> 00:48:51,000
He went crazy in the store,
but he seems all right now.

829
00:48:52,000 --> 00:48:55,800
This is what he was doin':
bam, bam...

830
00:48:55,800 --> 00:48:58,500
bam, bam.

831
00:48:58,500 --> 00:49:00,800
Yeah, bam, bam, bam, bam, bam.

832
00:49:00,800 --> 00:49:03,900
I told 'em not to touch
the fuckin' alarm, they did.

833
00:49:03,800 --> 00:49:08,300
If they hadn't have done what I told 'em
not to do, they'd still be alive.

834
00:49:09,800 --> 00:49:11,900
My fuckin' hero.

835
00:49:13,400 --> 00:49:15,400
Thanks.

836
00:49:15,400 --> 00:49:18,100
That's your excuse for going
on a kill-crazy rampage?

837
00:49:18,100 --> 00:49:20,200
I don't like alarms, Mr. White.

838
00:49:23,600 --> 00:49:25,900
What does it matter
who stays with the cop?

839
00:49:25,800 --> 00:49:27,900
We ain't lettin' him go.
He's seen everybody.

840
00:49:27,900 --> 00:49:29,900
I haven't been looking at you guys.

841
00:49:29,900 --> 00:49:32,400
Shut the fuck up, man!

842
00:49:32,300 --> 00:49:35,200
You guys should never have taken him
outta the trunk in the first place.

843
00:49:35,200 --> 00:49:39,200
- We tried to find out about the setup.
- There is no fuckin' setup!

844
00:49:39,100 --> 00:49:40,800
Now here's the news!

845
00:49:40,900 --> 00:49:44,000
Blondie, you stay here,
take care of these two!

846
00:49:43,800 --> 00:49:46,100
White and Pink, you come with me,
'cause if Joe gets here...

847
00:49:46,100 --> 00:49:48,300
and he sees all these
cars parked outside...

848
00:49:48,300 --> 00:49:51,300
I swear to you he's gonna be
just as mad at me as he is at you.

849
00:49:51,300 --> 00:49:53,300
Fine. Let's go.

850
00:50:13,200 --> 00:50:15,100
Alone at last.

851
00:50:35,600 --> 00:50:38,000
Guess what.

852
00:50:37,900 --> 00:50:40,600
I think I'm parked in the red zone.

853
00:50:45,500 --> 00:50:48,200
Now, where were we?

854
00:50:49,500 --> 00:50:52,900
I told you, I don't know anything
about any fuckin' setup.

855
00:50:54,200 --> 00:50:56,200
I've been on the force
for only eight months.

856
00:50:56,300 --> 00:50:58,500
They don't tell me anything.

857
00:50:59,900 --> 00:51:02,900
Nobody tells me shit.
You can torture me all you want.

858
00:51:02,800 --> 00:51:05,100
Torture you?
That's a good--

859
00:51:05,100 --> 00:51:08,200
That's a good idea.
I like that one, yeah.

860
00:51:09,500 --> 00:51:12,700
Even your boss said
there wasn't a setup.

861
00:51:14,500 --> 00:51:17,600
- My what?
- Your boss.

862
00:51:18,500 --> 00:51:20,400
Excuse me, pal.

863
00:51:20,400 --> 00:51:24,400
One thing I wanna make clear to you:
I don't have a boss.

864
00:51:24,400 --> 00:51:27,400
Nobody tells me what to do.
You understand?

865
00:51:27,300 --> 00:51:29,800
You hear what I said,
you son of a bitch?

866
00:51:29,800 --> 00:51:32,900
All right, all right, all right,
you don't have a boss.

867
00:51:35,700 --> 00:51:37,900
Get that fuckin' shit off.

868
00:51:45,600 --> 00:51:48,700
Look, I'm not gonna
bullshit you, okay?

869
00:51:50,100 --> 00:51:53,300
I don't really give a good fuck
what you know or don't know...

870
00:51:54,500 --> 00:51:57,100
but I'm gonna
torture you anyway...

871
00:51:58,900 --> 00:52:00,400
regardless.

872
00:52:00,400 --> 00:52:02,700
Not to get information.

873
00:52:04,200 --> 00:52:06,200
It's amusing to me...

874
00:52:06,100 --> 00:52:08,600
to torture a cop.

875
00:52:08,500 --> 00:52:11,700
You can say anything you want
because I've heard it all before.

876
00:52:13,100 --> 00:52:15,300
All you can do is...

877
00:52:15,300 --> 00:52:17,500
pray for a quick death...

878
00:52:19,900 --> 00:52:22,500
which...

879
00:52:22,500 --> 00:52:24,600
you ain't gonna get.

880
00:52:39,200 --> 00:52:40,900
Oh, God.

881
00:52:48,800 --> 00:52:52,800
You ever listen to K-BILLY's
"Super Sounds of the '70s"?

882
00:52:55,900 --> 00:52:58,200
It's my personal favorite.

883
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:08,700
Joe Egan and Gerry Rafferty
were a duo known as Stealer's Wheel...

884
00:53:08,500 --> 00:53:12,600
when they recorded this Dylanesque,
pop, bubble-gum favorite...

885
00:53:12,500 --> 00:53:15,600
from April of 1974.

886
00:53:15,600 --> 00:53:17,500
That reached up to number five...

887
00:53:17,500 --> 00:53:20,900
as K-BILLY's "Super Sounds
of the '70s" continues.

888
00:54:07,800 --> 00:54:09,900
Hold still.

889
00:54:09,900 --> 00:54:12,000
Hold still, you fuck.

890
00:54:31,600 --> 00:54:34,000
Was that good for you too?

891
00:54:34,500 --> 00:54:36,400
Hey, what's goin' on?

892
00:54:36,400 --> 00:54:37,900
You hear that?

893
00:54:47,900 --> 00:54:50,300
Don't go anywhere.
I'll be right back.

894
00:56:30,100 --> 00:56:32,500
Don't! Stop! Stop!

895
00:56:33,800 --> 00:56:36,800
- What? What's the matter?
- Don't do this.

896
00:56:37,800 --> 00:56:39,700
That burn a little bit?

897
00:56:40,500 --> 00:56:42,100
Don't! Stop!

898
00:56:44,900 --> 00:56:46,700
Please stop.

899
00:56:46,600 --> 00:56:48,800
Just stop. Stop.

900
00:56:48,800 --> 00:56:50,700
Just talk to me.
Don't. Please.

901
00:56:50,700 --> 00:56:52,300
Don't burn me, please.

902
00:56:55,300 --> 00:56:59,000
I don't know anything about
any of you fucking guys.

903
00:56:58,900 --> 00:57:00,900
I'm not gonna say anything.

904
00:57:02,800 --> 00:57:04,000
No! Please, no.

905
00:57:04,100 --> 00:57:05,600
- You all through?
- Stop!

906
00:57:05,600 --> 00:57:06,700
You all through?

907
00:57:06,800 --> 00:57:10,300
Please.
I got a little kid at home.

908
00:57:10,700 --> 00:57:11,900
You all done?

909
00:57:11,800 --> 00:57:13,800
- Don't!
- Have some fire.

910
00:58:15,200 --> 00:58:17,100
Oh, shit.

911
00:58:19,100 --> 00:58:20,600
Hey, you.

912
00:58:23,200 --> 00:58:25,500
What's your name?

913
00:58:28,500 --> 00:58:29,800
Marvin.

914
00:58:31,600 --> 00:58:32,800
Marvin what?

915
00:58:36,900 --> 00:58:38,400
Marvin Nash.

916
00:58:44,700 --> 00:58:46,600
Listen to me, Marvin.
I'm a--

917
00:58:49,200 --> 00:58:52,100
Listen to me, Marvin Nash.
I'm a cop.

918
00:58:53,800 --> 00:58:55,500
Yeah, I know.

919
00:58:57,800 --> 00:58:59,400
You do?

920
00:59:00,500 --> 00:59:03,800
Yeah.
Your name's Freddy somethin'.

921
00:59:04,700 --> 00:59:06,300
Newendyke.

922
00:59:07,400 --> 00:59:09,400
Freddy Newendyke.

923
00:59:12,900 --> 00:59:15,200
Frankie Ferchetti...

924
00:59:15,200 --> 00:59:19,000
introduced us
about five months ago.

925
00:59:21,700 --> 00:59:24,100
I don't remember that at all.

926
00:59:27,100 --> 00:59:29,000
I do.

927
00:59:31,800 --> 00:59:34,300
Freddy.

